replies.body:
My problem is the support role is meant to be *flexible*. When I choose a support, I have no idea what I'm going to buy until we're 10+ minutes in the game. 
If I'm {{champion:201}} and Zed is getting fed mid? Looks like I'm getting {{item:3110}} this game.
 If I'm {{champion:25}} and we're dominating bot? Time to rush {{item:3157}} 
If I'm {{champion:267}} and feel like being a beast, I'll build {{item:3116}} 

They completely destroyed Soraka's flexibility. You can only build one way every game, and that's squishy healer that can't heal herself (without poke). They discourage you to build health. They restrict her ratios to prevent mid Soraka. It's sad how small the cage Riot made for her is.

Now maybe in those (rare) games when there's not stuff like {{champion:238}} mid, {{champion:92}} top, and {{champion:254}} jungle to wreck you in 0.1 seconds- Soraka could be useful. Maybe. But then again I could just grab {{champion:412}} and a {{item:3031}} and go 10/0, and Riot doesn't seem to have a problem with that flexibility.
